  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing Participation in InternalRevenue Mobilization and Utilization in East Gonja Municipal</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Capacity building for revenue collectors and Civil Society groups
Social monitoring of Internal Generated Fund (IGF
Public information campaigns through Citizen Journalism(CJs)
Support citizen journalists and CBOs to create awareness among trade associations, businesses and citizens on the importance of revenue mobilization and their responsibilities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of the project is to strengthen citizen participation in MMDAs internal revenue generation and utilization for improved local government accountability and performance.
It is also intended to enhance citizens&apos; participation in district assembly revenue generation and utilization processes. This will ultimately improve accountability for financial resources in the Municipal Assembly with focus on internally generated funds (IGF). The specific changes that the project seeks to achieve include the following:
1.Tools and platforms developed for monitoring internal revenue generation and utilization in theEast Gonja Municipal Assembly
2.An increase in the number of interested citizens, who are engaging the MA in revenue generation on relevant platforms/Reference to other projects with data?
3.The availability and use of accessible information on internal revenue generation and utilization in the East Gonja Municipal Assembly increased</narrative>
  </description>
